sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K389016
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: ''A. tumefaciens'' C58 TI-plasmid, partsregistry, Mr. Gene
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This BioBrick is for testing the virA/G signaling system. The read-out is the mRFP <partinfo>E1010</partinfo>. This system contains an unmutated ''virA'', so it is possible to measure, how the natural virA/G system works and reacts.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: this is only for measuring the natural virA/G system
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jonas Aretz

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K389013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: partsregistry, synthetic gene by Mr. Gene, TI-plasmid from ''Agrobacterium tumefaciens'' C58
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: With this system it is possible to measure the activity of a virA receptor and the vir promoter, respectively. The reporter is the mRFP from the partsregistry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: medium strong constitutive promotor, terminator to keep basal expression of mRFP low
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jonas Aretz

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: virA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This BioBrick contains a ''virA'' receptor from ''Agrobacterium tumefaciens'' C58 under the control of a constitutive promotor.
We used it to mutate ''virA'' by error-prone PCR. For screening the mutants BBa_K389011 is also needed.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The ''virA'' gene is under the control a medium strong constitutive promotor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jonas Aretz

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator with two copies of <bb_part>BBa_B0010</bb_part>
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Austin Che

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: virA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a gene for the ''virA'' receptor from ''Agrobacterium tumefaciens'' C58. An illegal ''PstI'' restriction site was removed by site-directed mutagenesis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jonas Aretz

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: virG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the ''virG'' response regulator from the virA/G receptor system. The virA/G receptor system is used by ''Agrobacterium tumefaciens'' to detect phenolic substances secreted by plants. In presence of these substances, ''virG'' is activated by the ''virA'' receptor and induces the transcription of genes under the control of a ''vir'' promotor. Normally, ''virG'' needs the ''rpoA'' RNA polymerase subunit from ''A. tumefaciens'' to work in ''Escherichia coli'' but this ''virG'' BioBrick is mutated, so works with the ''rpoA'' subunit from ''E. coli''.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: synthesized by Mr. Gene, so optimated codon usage, removal of illegal restriction sites
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jonas Aretz

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Pvir
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a ''vir'' promotor from ''Agrobacterium tumefaciens'' C58. It is located on the TI-plasmid before the ''virB'' genes. It is activated by phosphorylated ''virG'' response regulator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jonas Aretz

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
